impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R_038
impressions.summary_personal: fantastic wine from tasmania, light bodied with plenty of red fruit, raspberry, strawberry, sweet spice, cardamon, quite complex on the note and palate with a lingering finish. tannins are smooth

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R_038
impressions.summary_personal:
Elegant Pinot notes with red currants, red cherry and raspberry notes.
Light oak and spice notes.
Cool elegance shows why Tassie might be the new burgundy. There is an earthy brightness, a fresh fruity ness, Cherries freshly plucked and wrapped in delicate cinnamon.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R_038
impressions.summary_personal:
charming fresh redcurrant and raspberry's aromas with gentle sweet morocco
spices. very smooth raspberry flavour's, complex and elegant with fine tannins

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R_038
impressions.summary_personal: Already on the nose an elegant and alluring aroma fresh red berries, sappy tarragon and tomato leaves. Very cool climate, pacific freshness, light but complex with fine grainy tannin and great length. It is a winner baby

impressions.name: 2020_FR-BY-R_012
impressions.summary_personal: Fruity and wonderfull wine
impressions.food_pairing: Suitable for chicken and roasts

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-R_021
impressions.summary_personal:
perfumed wild black and red berry's, intense black pepper bell.
meaty, rich sweet spices with complex oak aromas. complex tannins with a very long finish.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-R_021
impressions.summary_personal:
Bold big red with a bit of chunk on the right parts. Not for purists but for the ones who love ripe fruit, spicy oak and a bit of muscle. 
As a house more a winter option and hits the Pricepoint

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-R_021
impressions.summary_personal: elegant and smooth, black cherries, plums, vanilla, coconut flavours. on the nose is quite concentrated, on thepalate is full bodied with plenty of dark fruit and firm tannins. Great value for money

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-R_021
impressions.summary_personal: Deep, rich notes of warm, ripe berries and Christmas spices. Big oak notes add sweet vanilla and clove to the heady mixture of black currants and black berries. A warm, rich inviting winter wine crying out for steak or winter warming stews.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-GRE_004
impressions.summary_personal: A wine that was very much in contention for best in show. Elegant Grenache full of fruitcake and Christmas cake notes. Bright, if slightly raisined berries red and sweet red currant. Elegant spice with gentle tannins and soft liquorice spices. A wine that wants to wrap you up and keep you warm over winter.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R_038
impressions.summary_personal: See my fine wine of the year note.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_015
impressions.summary_personal: A bit of a unicorn or a least an Unexpected  sight. Wild but not to wild natural cheeky number, playing tunes of preserved lemon, picked yellow plum, camomile and roast chicken skin. Fresh with a light phenolic grip on the palette still juicy. A wine for the menu pairings or to go with the entire meal.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_015
impressions.summary_personal: wonderful perfumed of stone fruit, peach, floral, lime, orange peel, with a creamy texture on the palate, with an outstanding acidity. very complex on both palate and nose, very long pleasant finish.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_015
impressions.summary_personal:
charming and complex dry apricot, honeysuckle, dry chamomile aromas.
fresh mango and pineapple flavour's. refreshing green apple acidity. Long finish with seaweed minerality.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_015
impressions.summary_personal: A lovely, warm, rich, oak aged Chenin blanc with dried apple flavours, dried floral notes and some rich custard springing up on the finish. Elegant freshness is a surprising element to the overall effect of this wine. Balance and freshness drives  the dried fruit notes of this  surprisingly balanced wine.

impressions.name: 2020_HW-R_033
impressions.summary_personal:
Backed red and black berries, ideas of leather and herbal oak spice.
Generous and charming fruit, with soft tannins and fully mature.

impressions.name: 2020_HW-R_033
impressions.summary_personal: For the price, this is a well made wine with winter spices and ripe red fruits. Simple yet subtly complex with integrated oak flavours. Rich spice notes add an extra layer to the overall package.

impressions.name: 2020_HW-R_033
impressions.summary_personal: Quite herbaceous and green on the nose, with a hint of raspberries, black fruit forest. On the palate is quite approachable, with round tannins.

impressions.name: 2020_HW-R_033
impressions.summary_personal:
Rich ripe plum with Turkish sweet spices aromas and dry black tobacco leaves. with complex a palate and attitude tannins, because of the again.
Great value as house wine

impressions.name: 2020_HW-W_033
impressions.summary_personal:
It is an aromaticly Ecstatic wine, giving you big Sauvignon herbaceous notes with tropic and citrus fruit in the back yard.
Juicy and fresh, punters will order the second bottles rather quickly

impressions.name: 2020_HW-W_033
impressions.summary_personal: fresh gooseberry and green tea leave aromas, refreshing acidity with the lime zest and minerality underline.  Great value as house wine.

impressions.name: 2020_HW-W_033
impressions.summary_personal: dry and crisp, lively notes of fresh grass, gooseberry, lime, lemon. On the palate is quite pure and fruit-forward with a sharp acidity. Very good value for money it is a style of wine that can e drunk anytime during the day.

impressions.name: 2020_HW-W_033
impressions.summary_personal: Very new world in style with loads of grass and asparagus on the nose and palate. A bright, cool climate wine with fresh green fruit flavours interlaced with some hints of passion fruit and a bright mineral note. Easy drinking and refreshing. Crisp and elegant.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-RHO-S-R_002
impressions.summary_personal:
The familiar nose of raspberry, black currants, dried herbs and  warm stones. 
Big red with good thank a juice.
impressions.food_pairing: Robust southern Rhône are miracle workers. Think rack of lamb

impressions.name: 2020_FR-RHO-S-R_002
impressions.summary_personal: Bright raspberry fruit with spice and vanilla elements, some liquorice on the finish
impressions.food_pairing: A bit left field but the super ripe raspberry fruits might work well with the chocolate fondant. Otherwise the rack of lamb would work well with the fruits and acidity.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-RHO-S-R_002
impressions.food_pairing: Classic South of France match Roast Chicken with herbs  and spice and jammy rhone red. Vive la France...........

impressions.name: 2020_FR-RHO-S-R_002
impressions.summary_personal: black cherry, black pepper, blackcurrant, earthy notes, with grippy tannins.
impressions.food_pairing: perfect combination with rack of lamb, well balance between the structure and tannins of the wine with the tenderness of the meat, meanwhile the fattiness of the meat make the wine become smoother.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-CHI-LEY_003
impressions.summary_personal: Red cherry and berry spice. Balsamic vinegar, red blossom.  Oak spice and vanilla.
impressions.food_pairing: Here the rack of lamb would work well. The red currant note would work well with the meat and there is enough acidity to soften the sweet lamb fat. The low tannins would be washed away by the meat making the wine appear fruitier.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-CHI-LEY_003
impressions.summary_personal: Ripe and spiced Pinot style. Simple and recognisable
impressions.food_pairing: Pinot sleeps with every food you can think of. For me with ripe fruity Oakes wines like this meaty or gamey dishes are best. It will go down with your beef burger without any forplay

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-CHI-LEY_003
impressions.food_pairing: fresh gentle red plum with black pepper bell will complement the elegant flavour's of roast lamb, with the spices of the wine offering extra complexity.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-CHI-LEY_003
impressions.food_pairing: light and fresh, supple and round, slightly leathery on the palate with smooth t match tannins great match with margherita pizza. the cheese brings up the smoky flavours in the wine

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-CH-CL-R_001
impressions.summary_personal:
Sweet red cherry, Dusty oak, dried herbs and flowers.
Dry, lively, dusty tannin and full in body
impressions.food_pairing: Tuscan classic work wonders with meaty dishes and Mediterranean flavours. From Pizza Marguerita to steak this will work

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-CH-CL-R_001
impressions.summary_personal: Soft red cherry fruits with light tannins
impressions.food_pairing: The rack of lamb would work well with this wine. The cherry fruits would take the place of the red currant jelly and the acidity would balance the sweet lamb fat.

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-CH-CL-R_001
impressions.food_pairing: Intense red plum flavour's with firm tannins will paired with juice beef burger on a pub.

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-CH-CL-R_001
impressions.food_pairing: perfectly matched with pizza margherita, the tomato sauce brings up the acidity of the wines  and meanwhile the cheese makes the tannins taste smoother

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_011
impressions.summary_personal: Hints of stony minerality, green apple and pear, some floral notes. Fresh acidity.
impressions.food_pairing: The more mineral note and lack of obvious sweetness would make this work well with fish and chips on the beach at Brighton.

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_011
impressions.summary_personal: Charming fizz, fresh red grapefruit and bruising apple. Super easy and great value
impressions.food_pairing:
For me an aperitif sparkling. So easy
To drink. it will wash down anything nicely even little richer rice dishes like a risotto

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_011
impressions.summary_personal: light lemon flower with ripe peach notes, very lively palate well balance by the acidity
impressions.food_pairing: fruit aromas and the acidity work with rich chocolate fondant bringing some freshness with the acidity

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_011
impressions.summary_personal: light and refreshing with neutral flavours, a hint of minerality through the end.
impressions.food_pairing: good match with vegeterian risotto,

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R-MAU_007
impressions.summary_personal: Reductive notes of black currant spangles. Sweet dark fruits with vanilla and cinnamon spice.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R-MAU_007
impressions.food_pairing:
Sunday roast chicken with peppery, juice, fruit chile red.
the gentle green leafy, jammy red plum will work well with the gentle white meat of the chicken.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R-MAU_007
impressions.summary_personal: Ripe dark berries, reductive notes of black currant spangles.oak spices.
impressions.food_pairing: Ripe fruits and sweetness might work with with the beef burger. Sweetness of fruit with the beef and pickled onion and gherkin. and acidity with the fatty ness of the burger

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R-MAU_007
impressions.summary_personal: Sweet black currant, plum, red cherry and oak spice. Lively but also full in body. Polished tannin, loads of ripe fruit
impressions.food_pairing: Big fruit bomb usually lifts game dishes and fatty poultry like duck and goose roast.. also a good glass with your lamb rack

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-R-MAU_007
impressions.summary_personal: very green

impressions.name: 2020_TUR-R-OKBO_003
impressions.summary_personal:
Warm dark berries and dried flowers.
Dry, fresh acidity. Grippy tannin and slide dusty notes
impressions.food_pairing: Robust red with tannin and acidity leans to meaty and roasting flavours. Try roast rack of lamb or beef burger

impressions.name: 2020_TUR-R-OKBO_003
impressions.summary_personal: Medium intensity red and black berries with fresh acidity.
impressions.food_pairing: The margherita pizza would work well with this wine. There is enough a city to bring the sweetness out of the tomato and cut through the richness of the cheese.

impressions.name: 2020_TUR-R-OKBO_003
impressions.food_pairing:
fresh crush red berry's flavour's with gentle sweet sour plummy character.
will be a enjoyable pairing with a pullet pork.

impressions.name: 2020_TUR-R-OKBO_003
impressions.food_pairing: good match with a steak served with beetroot salad where it enhances the  fruit character of the wine, with smoother tannins

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-DUE-R_041
impressions.summary_personal:
Stewed red and black berry notes, leather, old wood notes and ideas of parsley and dill.
Big structure and robust tannins
impressions.food_pairing: Savoury and big red with herbal and oaky notes lean naturally to red meat and game dishes but also a dirty beef burger will make a great match

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-DUE-R_041
impressions.summary_personal: Soft, ripe sark fruits with a fresh acidity on the finish.
impressions.food_pairing: This wine is light enough to match the rack of lamb where the acidity will cut through the sweet lamb fat and the fruits compliment the flavours of the lamb. Itself.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-DUE-R_041
impressions.food_pairing: charming flavour's and aromas. Sweet spices and fresh red plum with great complexity. Will paired with rack of Lamb. Fine elegant cut of meat with a charming ribera del duero.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-DUE-R_041
impressions.food_pairing: dry and concentrated, plenty of cherries, high alcohol and firms tannins matching well with the steak and makes the meat taste more tender and juicer.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-TOR_001
impressions.summary_personal: Super floral. Elderflower, Jasmin, rose. Crisp flavours citrus and bashed herbs
impressions.food_pairing: Big aromatics and crisp acidity goes with many  veggie dishes. Try with veggie risotto or your tofu that green Curry

impressions.name: 2020_NW-TOR_001
impressions.summary_personal: Floral, lemon and citrus, some pear fruit as well.
impressions.food_pairing: Perhaps the ceviche would work with this wine. There is enough acidity to match the dish and the floral freshness would add an extra dimension.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-TOR_001
impressions.food_pairing:
the complex floral aromas will  paired well with salmon ceviche 
Having the acidity from the ceviche and floral aromas from the wine coming tougher as one flavour's harmony.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-TOR_001
impressions.summary_personal: fantastic torrontes, with notes  of lime cordial, lemon, slightly floral and less perfumed then typical. high acidity and intensity
impressions.food_pairing: good match with ceviche, the citrus notes of the wines perfectly match with the coriander sauce on the ceviche and enhancing the flavours of the dish.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-GR-R_001
impressions.summary_personal: Fully developed wine. Meaty savoury aromatics and flavour. Ripe and soft tannin with leathery fruit, autumn Forrest and herbal spice.
impressions.food_pairing: Mature reds with dominant earthy savoury aromatics lean towards foods for the colder part of the year. Mushrooms, truffle and game. Still they will also bring out the best from a rack of lamb

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-GR-R_001
impressions.summary_personal: Mature notes of dried red and black berries and currants with very soft tannins.
impressions.food_pairing: This wine is too subtle for the steak but the rack of lamb is made for this wine.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-GR-R_001
impressions.food_pairing: Fresh style of rioja. Very smooth primary fruit. Will match with veggie risotto. The gentle primary fruit will be a charming complement for the savory and vegetal flavour's.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-N-R_009
impressions.summary_personal: Soft, juicy red fruits with lots of tannins. Quite chunky
impressions.food_pairing: The chunky ness of this wine would help it with the rack of lamb there is enough body and tannins to work twitch the meat which would soften the wine and the fruity elements would compliment the sweet flavours of the lamb.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-N-R_009
impressions.summary_personal: Stewed red and black fruit, leather, mocha with a lite drying tannin
impressions.food_pairing: Reds with a marked tannin a usually great for dishes with mustard in the making and of cause protein rich dishes like rack of lamb or steak

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-N-R_009
impressions.food_pairing: firm tannins. Ripe and spice cherry flavour's will match with pulled pork.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-N-R_009
impressions.food_pairing: earthy, herbaceous with high tannins and acidity with hint of dark fruit marrying well with rack of lamb

impressions.name: 2020_ROS_034
impressions.summary_personal: Red currant and cherry and strawberry fruits. Some mineral notes.
impressions.food_pairing: Can’t see this working with any of the dishes.

impressions.name: 2020_ROS_034
impressions.summary_personal: Muscle-Rosé. Good structure, redfruot and bitter citrus notes. Touch of dried herbs and sun on stones
impressions.food_pairing: Power rose can make a great Allrounde if it got enough acidity. Try with Roast salmon, pulled pork or even pizza Marguerita

impressions.name: 2020_ROS_034
impressions.food_pairing: rich deep red wild berry flavour's will complement the gentile flavour's of roast lamb, will act as redcurrant gelly and the high acidity will reduce the intensity of the fat. enjoy :)

impressions.name: 2020_ROS_034
impressions.summary_personal: cherry, red current, violet, medium bodied and intensity.
impressions.food_pairing: no matching

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-R_002
impressions.summary_personal: Soft cherry and berry fruit with rich oak and spice. Fresh cherry finish, a bit sour (Minimum intervention?)
impressions.food_pairing: Again the sour cherry flavours would work well with the roast lamb. And the acidly cut through the sweet lamb fat. A spicy finish adds an extra element to the dish.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-R_002
impressions.food_pairing: calling for meat!!!! rich, ripe, power with black pepper flavour's needs to be match with chargrill steak and happiness take place.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-R_002
impressions.summary_personal: intense and elegant, green pepper bell, herbaceous notes, blackcurrant, black cherry, sour plum, high acidity and firm tannins.
impressions.food_pairing: great match with a  salty steak which makes the wines taste smoother, richer

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-R_002
impressions.summary_personal: Herbal dark berry notes, sappy tomato leaves, fresh. Livley on the palette. Grainy tannin. Good stuff
impressions.food_pairing: Juicy Loire wines great with medium rare steak or earthy veggie dishes

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-W_012
impressions.summary_personal: Tropical and oxidative note take you right to Rioja. Robust, textured with a good freshes
impressions.food_pairing: A bolder white is great for pronounced foods with meaty or roasted flavours. Think roast chicken or pulled pork...

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-W_012
impressions.summary_personal: Yellow. Fruits, toasty oak, vanilla creamy ness. Some mushroom notes and a fresh lemon acidity. Almost a salty Moroccan  preserved lemon.
impressions.food_pairing: Torn here between the Thai green curry where the creamy ness would match the coconut richness and there is enough ripeness to work with the spicy element. On the other hand this could also work with the vegetarian risotto where the creamy, rich Parmesan sauce would be matched with oak and the salty lemon would cut through the richness.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-W_012
impressions.food_pairing: the rich fresh almond notes and dried apricot flavour's will be a complement to a vegetarian risotto supporting to Shane the savory flavour's.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-W_012
impressions.summary_personal: full bodied with maderised apple, influence of oak is present,touch of  lime, lemon
impressions.food_pairing: good match with avocado on toast served with tomato and green apple salad.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-SAV-CHI-LEY_008
impressions.summary_personal: Uber-aromatics. Trip to the wineries of the cool Atlantic coast and a spa in the same time. Lemon grass, gooseberry, nettle and tinned beans
impressions.food_pairing: Sauvignon Blanc has a great talent to put out the fire of a hot green curry and in the same time it mirrors the green herbal flavour of the curry

impressions.name: 2020_NW-SAV-CHI-LEY_008
impressions.summary_personal: Rich pea pod notes, classic cool climate Sauvignon blanc. Dry, mineral finish. Green fruits.
impressions.food_pairing:
Again this might work with the veggie risotto, the acidity would cut through the rich sauce and the pea pod would add an extra vegetable to the risotto.
On the other hand I could see this working just as well with the fish and chips. Here the acidity would cut through the oily ness of the fried fish. And the pea pod add the mushy pea element to the fish and chips.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-SAV-CHI-LEY_008
impressions.food_pairing: rich green pepper bell and lemon grass  flavour's will be a match to a fresh salmon ceviche, the acidity of the ceviche will create a harmony with med palate of the wine.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-SAV-CHI-LEY_008
impressions.summary_personal: quite herbaceous, grassy, tomato leaf, gooseberry, very clean and dry on the palate with a great lenght
impressions.food_pairing: fantastic match with ceviche, the acidity of the wine enhance the flavours of the seabass.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-CAT-R_020
impressions.summary_personal: Rich red and black fruits with bright acidity and tannins,
impressions.food_pairing: The tannins in this wine would be softened with a steak, the fruity and spicy elements would compliment the smoky, meaty flavours of the dish.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-CAT-R_020
impressions.summary_personal: Big ripe fruit, dried floral and cracked stone minerality. Big, sweet oak, polished with loads of character
impressions.food_pairing: Big oaky reds can work well with beef and other read meats. This strikes a Mediterranean character hence I would go for a roasted rack of lamb to match

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-CAT-R_020
impressions.food_pairing: Engaging red wine. very sophisticated with fine aromas and flovour's. Will paired with juice steak.  Will be a sinfonia of flavours.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-CAT-R_020
impressions.food_pairing: warm and oaky priorat matching greatly with beef burger with perfect balance

impressions.name: 2020_OFS-L_000A
impressions.summary_personal: Aromas of Orange Marmelade, dried flowers, warm stones. On the palette sweet and robust but charming
impressions.food_pairing: Good Muscat de setubal can be miracle paring for cheese and sweet egg based desert. Also you Never go wrong with chocolate desserts like chocolate Fondant

impressions.name: 2020_OFS-L_000A
impressions.summary_personal: Lovely notes of toffee apples, caramel and spice with a fresh acidity on the finish.
impressions.food_pairing: Chocolate fondue where are you? The sweetness will work well with the chocolate bitterness and the roasted nut/ bean flavours of the chocolate. Overall the wine would not appear to taste as sweet with the dish as on its own.

impressions.name: 2020_OFS-L_000A
impressions.food_pairing: the rich dry fruit and the light balsamic flavour's will paired with a chocolate fondant bring complexity and allowing the acidity of the wine to keep the palate fresh

impressions.name: 2020_OFS-L_000A
impressions.summary_personal: orange marmalade, pine, apricot, sweet spice, medium sweet, high acidity.
impressions.food_pairing: great match with chocolate fondant served with orange sauce, great balance between the acidity of the wine and sweetness of the chocolate.

impressions.name: 2020_IT-SS-R-NA_004
impressions.summary_personal: Soft , ripe black currants with vanilla and cinnamon spice.
impressions.food_pairing: The juicy bark fruits of this wine would work well with the beef burger. Soft and ripe they would compliment the juicy ness of the meat and the acidity would counteract any fatty ness.

impressions.name: 2020_IT-SS-R-NA_004
impressions.summary_personal:
Black current, bramble Sirup and warm.
Big southern red. Rustic, ripe and ready
impressions.food_pairing: Here is lot of ripe fruit and structure I. The wine from the south. Naturaly one for earthy veggie dishes like beetroot but also one for savoury gamy dishes or Roaster rack of Lamb

impressions.name: 2020_IT-SS-R-NA_004
impressions.food_pairing: fresh and soft, jammy red wine. paired with Sunday roast chicken British classic.

impressions.name: 2020_IT-SS-R-NA_004
impressions.food_pairing: great match with roasted salmon, brings the ripe red fruit flavours of cherry, strawberry, raspberry. quite round and supple on the palate with very silky tannins

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-NW-ALB_005
impressions.summary_personal: Crisp Green apple and lemon, salty notes of brine.
impressions.food_pairing: The fresh acidity would work with the ceviche or the fish and chips. In the case of the ceviche we would be matching the acidity in the cure and the fish and chips we would be cutting through the oily fried fish and seasoning it with lemon and salt.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-NW-ALB_005
impressions.summary_personal: Peach, grapefruit and Granny Smith notes. Crisp, stony palette with a bit of terchery notes
impressions.food_pairing: High acidity and fruit complexity rocks your fried food dishes from Fish n chips to Tempura

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-NW-ALB_005
impressions.food_pairing: fresh sea breeze and crispy zestyness will a match with fish & chips a pairing made on the sea :)

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-NW-ALB_005
impressions.summary_personal: greener style of Albarino, good acidity quiet zesty.
impressions.food_pairing: no matching

impressions.name: 2020_FR-BY-CHA_001
impressions.food_pairing: rich citrus flavour's and the gentle oak aromas will work with roast salmon bring the light cream flavour's to complement the fish

impressions.name: 2020_FR-BY-CHA_001
impressions.summary_personal: medium body, crisp and dry with medium-high acidity, a hint of oak on the nose. quite intense on the palate with plenty of green fruit.
impressions.food_pairing: perfect match with thai chicken green curry which reduces the touch of  spiciness of the dish.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-BY-CHA_001
impressions.summary_personal: Ripeish tropical fruit melon and pineapple. Creamy vanilla oak, fresh acidity.
impressions.food_pairing: The richness of the wine would work well with the roast salmon where the creamy oak would match the oily ness of the salmon but the acidity is light enough to keep the fish juicy.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-BY-CHA_001
impressions.summary_personal:
Ripe melon, pineapple and vanillary spice.
Fresh and textured. Well made classic.
impressions.food_pairing: Classic Oakes burgundy does a trick with creamy sauces and fatty fishy think roast salmon or roast chicken with creamed mushrooms

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-CR-R_003
impressions.summary_personal: Leather, red fruit, herbal notes. Fresh acity and grippy tannin. Old fashioned, robust Rioja.
impressions.food_pairing: The old school reds. Really work for comfort dishes. Think pizza Marguerita or beef burger

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-CR-R_003
impressions.summary_personal: Spicy cinnamon and clove with red and dark cherry fruit. Fresh acidity.
impressions.food_pairing: This wine is crying out for a rack of lamb. The red fruit cherries bring a fresh acidity which balances the the sweet lamb fat and the salty blood of the lamb softens the tannins allowing the fruit element of the wine to develop.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-CR-R_003
impressions.food_pairing: rioja and margherita the new marriage made in London. Margherita pizza rich tomato sauce and bread savory flavour's will match with crush red plum flavour's and spices from the rioja.

impressions.name: 2020_SPN-RIO-CR-R_003
impressions.summary_personal: great red rioja wine, fulld bodied and rich, hint of oak and red fruit. great length
impressions.food_pairing: no matching

impressions.summary_personal: Oxidative style, savoury. Slide spiced notes.
impressions.food_pairing: Very savoury wine great for your meaty dishes like pulled pork but also your classic Pizza Marguerita

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-W-K_002
impressions.summary_personal: Orange wine style, orange peel and spice. Oxydied bruised fruits.
impressions.food_pairing: Can’t see it working with anything on the list

impressions.name: 2020_NW-O-W-K_002

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-D-R_015
impressions.summary_personal: Big notes of ripe red and black fruits with vanilla oak and big tannins.
impressions.food_pairing: This big wine needs a big steak. The tannins will appear softer and the dark cherry and currant fruits will enhance the flavours of the meat.

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-D-R_015
impressions.summary_personal:
Dark fruit, dried herbs, bay leave, oak spice.
Robust texture, olive, herbs and solid tannin
impressions.food_pairing: Big bold red with character. Simple to match.... Steak!

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-D-R_015
impressions.food_pairing: elegant expression from the douro valley. full of character but with a sophisticated approach will be an excellent match with rich beef burger.

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-D-R_015
impressions.summary_personal: green on the nose and palate
impressions.food_pairing: no food matching

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-SAF_004
impressions.summary_personal: Tarry smoky notes dominate. Dark cherries, spicy oak.
impressions.food_pairing: A chargrilled beef burger would work well with the smoky element of the wine. and the acidity of the gherkin works well with the acidity of the wine.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-SAF_004
impressions.summary_personal: Smoky ripe style of Pinot Noir. Pretty, juicy, sweet fruity  and surprisingly fresh
impressions.food_pairing: This Pinot from a very hot climate is a good quaffer and will make slightly chilled a great BBQ red. Till it is back in season try with Peking  duck or pulled pork

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-SAF_004
impressions.food_pairing: the light fruity Pinot Noir aromas will paired with a margarita pizza and a movie. match made for a raining Sunday night

impressions.name: 2020_NW-PIN-SAF_004
impressions.summary_personal: red cherry, plum, floral notes, quite supple and warm on the palate, smooth tannins and round.
impressions.food_pairing: great match with a beef burger served with chutney,

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-W-V_007
impressions.summary_personal: Character white with floral, bitter almond and citrus notes. Grippy palette, appertaining and lingering
impressions.food_pairing: The wine is quiet dramatic with freshness, grip and an elegant bitterness. Free at with Mediterranean veggie dishes and risotto.

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-W-V_007
impressions.food_pairing: the lime zest and green pepper bell will be a match with a rich fish & chips. the acidity and zest notes will work with the butter of the fish.

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-W-V_007
impressions.summary_personal: slightly herbaceous, green apple, good acidity.
impressions.food_pairing: no matching

impressions.name: 2020_IT-CEN-W-V_007
impressions.summary_personal: Crisp lemon acidity, some mineral notes. Fresh finish. Some pear notes.
impressions.food_pairing: A simple wine with a fresh acidity which would compliment the acidity of the ceviche. Adding a lemon note to the dish.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-CHE_001
impressions.summary_personal: Crisp, mineral flavours with green apples and a touch of oak. Creamy notes on the finish
impressions.food_pairing: The extra body from the oak would help this wine stand up to the richness of the roast salmon. With enough acidity to balance the oily ness of the fish without drying the fish out.

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-CHE_001
impressions.summary_personal:
Textured and stoney white with a blend of fruity and savoury notes. 
Great to pair with an array of foods
impressions.food_pairing: That savouriness and fruit complexity will do a good trick with roast chicken and polled pork. The wine will enhance the flavours as well as giving a great foil and clean up your palette after

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-CHE_001
impressions.summary_personal: rich dried tropical notes with cream savory flavour's, rich herbal basil characters
impressions.food_pairing:
the creamy and herbal basil flavour's will be an harmony with margarita pizza 
the acidity will keep the palate refresh all the way :)

impressions.name: 2020_FR-LOI-CHE_001
impressions.summary_personal: dry and intense, slightly buttery, toasty, with stone fruit flavours. great acidity and intensity with a long finish.
impressions.food_pairing: Fabolous companion with Roasted Salmon with green beans. the wines has great complexity  and the oak characteristics bring the sweetness in the salmon.

impressions.name: 2020_AUS-GV_001
impressions.summary_personal: Lean and flinty Grüner with grapefruit pith and flint smoke notes. Firm, grippy palette with bit of richness
impressions.food_pairing: That lean style and aromatic gun flint notes can make an interesting addition to your matching wines. Try with ceviche

impressions.name: 2020_AUS-GV_001
impressions.summary_personal: Slight oily ness with ginger spice and lemon and apple fruits. Fresh acidity
impressions.food_pairing: Perhaps the roads at salmon, but I would prefer a nice fat wurst type sausage or pork knuckle.

impressions.name: 2020_AUS-GV_001
impressions.summary_personal: aromatic gruner slightly white peppery on both nose and palate, with floral notes
impressions.food_pairing: nomatching

impressions.name: 2020_AUS-GV_001
impressions.summary_personal: ED TEST 1
impressions.food_pairing: ED TEST 2

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_009
impressions.food_pairing: Roast chicken with herbs with rich cream from the lees and the light MLF flavour's will complement and add complicity to the pairing

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_009
impressions.summary_personal: slightly oaky on the nose with touch of vanilla, peach, apricot, silky and buttery on the palate. great intensity and long finish.
impressions.food_pairing: great match with rack of lamb served with roasted potatoes, carrots. The oak intensity of chenin it stands up to the succulent juicy lamb

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_009
impressions.summary_personal: Fresh green apples and mineral notes.
impressions.food_pairing: The crispness of this wine might work well with the smashed avocado on toast. There is enough acidity to balance the oily avo the fruit will pick up on the flavours.

impressions.name: 2020_NW-CB_009
impressions.summary_personal:
Reductive. Lemon cordial, toast, hay on the nose.
Livley, textured white, crisp acidity and medium length.
impressions.food_pairing: Fresh and lightly creamy white makes a good partner to flavour intense fish dishes like roast salmon. Also can give a great foil for mildly spiced green curry.

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-VVE_008
impressions.summary_personal: Wow. Super aromatics of citrus, peach and lees. Fresh textured, very good for the price point
impressions.food_pairing: The wine is fresh, lively and aromatic. Great for fried foods like Fish n chips and dishes with a bit of hot spice like a Thai green curry

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-VVE_008
impressions.summary_personal: Lightly spicy, mineral freshness, some floral notes. Lemon and apricot. Fresh citrus acidity.
impressions.food_pairing: The acidity would work well with the freshness of the Ceviche. Adding an extra lemon twist to the dish.

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-VVE_008
impressions.summary_personal: rich lemon peel, with ripe notes of nectarine, well balance
impressions.food_pairing: great match with the veggie risotto the ripe fruit aromas and zest flavour's will match the savory flavour's of the risotto

impressions.name: 2020_PGL-VVE_008
impressions.summary_personal: quite aromatic with jasmine notes, apricot, touch of lime zest, lychee, quite perfumed on both palate and nose.
impressions.food_pairing: fantastic match with fish and chips, the acidity of the wines cleans the oily fish texture,

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_002
impressions.summary_personal:
Pear notes, some citrus, stone fruits some floral notes.
Quite rich. Creamy fizz.
impressions.food_pairing: The creaminess and acidity might work with the avocado on toast. Balancing out the oily fruit.

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_002
impressions.summary_personal:
Floral, citrus, Cracked stones 
Vibrant, prominent fizz, with appetising bitterness
impressions.food_pairing:
The appetising bitterness and freshness will work great with fried foods as well as dishes of raw food and acity. 
Think Fish and chips or ceviche
Also work with brunch dishes like Avo on toast

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_002
impressions.summary_personal: fresh apricots and dry pineapple, refreshing on the palate, light and gentle mousse. the apricot and nectarine flavor's dominate with balance by the minerality
impressions.food_pairing: will go well  with avocado on toast the fruit notes of the wine and the savory flavor's

impressions.name: 2020_SPA-IT-P_002
impressions.summary_personal: ripe stone fruit of peach, pear, floral notes, good acidity and refreshing
impressions.food_pairing: great matching with Ceviche, cut through the fattiness of the fish.
